         libglfw3 | libglfw3-wayland
Description: Python ctypes bindings for GLFW3
 GLFW is a portable library for OpenGL, Vulkan, and window/input
 management. This package provides Python ctypes bindings that wrap the
 system GLFW3 shared library, exposing the full GLFW API under Pythonic
 naming conventions.
 .
 Supports X11 and Wayland on Linux (via libglfw3 or libglfw3-wayland),
 and is a common foundation for OpenGL game windows, shader demos, and
 real-time rendering tools that don't use a higher-level framework like
 pygame or pyglet.
